---
import OnboardingLayout from '@/layouts/OnboardingLayout.astro';

const pageTitle = 'Dashboard Overview';
---

<OnboardingLayout title={pageTitle} section="dashboard" readTime="4 min">
  <p class="text-gray-300 mb-6">
    The dashboard is your command center. It surfaces open orders, invoice alerts, and quick links
    so you can act fast.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
    <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-dark p-6 shadow-sm">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">Tiles you will see</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-300">
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-primary">•</span>
          <span
            ><strong>Orders</strong> – Pending, In Production, Shipped, Completed counts with shortcuts
            to filtered views.</span
          >
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-primary">•</span>
          <span
            ><strong>Invoices</strong> – Outstanding balance, upcoming due dates, and a link to upload
            new invoices.</span
          >
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-primary">•</span>
          <span><strong>Account</strong> – Profile completion status and portal access settings.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-primary">•</span>
          <span><strong>Inventory</strong> – SKUs flagged for low stock or aging quantities.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-dark p-6 shadow-sm">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">Alerts and shortcuts</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-400 mb-3">
        Alerts show on the right rail and in the header badge. Click any alert to jump into the
        related record.
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-300">
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-primary">•</span>
          <span
            >Use <strong>Quick Actions</strong> to start a new order or review invoices and reports.</span
          >
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-primary">•</span>
          <span
            >Pin your favorite reports and shortcuts; they will stay on top each time you log in.</span
          >
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-primary">•</span>
          <span>Hover over any chart to export or copy the data.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-8 grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
    <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-dark p-4">
      <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-gray-500 font-semibold mb-1">
        Customization
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">
        Drag to reorder tiles. Collapse metrics you do not need to keep the view clean.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-dark p-4">
      <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-gray-500 font-semibold mb-1">Filters</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">
        Save dashboard filters (date ranges, brands) so you can swap contexts in one click.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-dark p-4">
      <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-gray-500 font-semibold mb-1">Mobile</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">
        On mobile, tap the menu to access tiles; the same alerts appear at the top.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</OnboardingLayout>
